snippet.textDisplay: This is by far one of my favorites. Not just because it is a very good song to listen to, and also very honest, but also because I relate to it. I've been through a lot mentally regarding dreams, nightmares, sleep paralysis, depression and suicide. I've had these thoughts about leaving and no one caring, and it hurt me. And then, my sister would be my guardian. She helped me through it all, always by my side and trying her best to protect me. Even though we used to fight so much when we were kids, this brought us close and now I can't tell anyone that hey're my "best friend", because now I can see how heavy those words are and how only one person was really 100% worthy of them. It's a shame that people feel so weirded out by brother/sister bonding. It's common for the older sibling to feel compelled to protect and care for the younger one. I am very proud of Billie for opening up about this. Her soul shines through it.

snippet.textDisplay:
Here's my video - lyrics analysis:


It might've been a nightmare
To anyone who might care 



Normally, if we'd witness a girl driving towards the water or if someone told you they had a dream, and in that dream, they drove their car towards the sea, we would describe this as a nightmare but to Billie,


I had a dream
I got everything I wanted
Not what you'd think
And if I'm being honest



And so, it's more like a good dream because, in her dream, there is no judgment, no expectations from the outsiders. She's safe from the world because it's just him and her.
